  "prompt": "Is it the norm to put your degrees in your email signature?",
  "response": "It depends on the context and professional field:\n\n1. Academic and professional settings:\n- Common in higher education\n- Typical for doctors, PhDs, and professionals with advanced degrees\n- More prevalent in fields like medicine, law, and academia\n\n2. Business and corporate settings:\n- Less common and often seen as unnecessary\n- Generally only used if the degree is directly relevant to your role\n\n3. Generally accepted practices:\n- For medical professionals (MD, DO, etc.)\n- For academic researchers (PhD)\n- For lawyers (JD)\n\n4. Best practices:\n- Only include if the degree is relevant to your current work\n- Use sparingly and professionally\n- Typically list highest/most relevant degree\n\nExample: \nJane Smith, MBA\nMarketing Director\n\nSo while it's not universally required, it can be appropriate in certain professional contexts.",
